---
// src/components/AboutIntro.astro
---

<section class="bg-mapa-canvas-dark border-t border-mapa-contour/60 py-16 md:py-24 font-serif">
	<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
			
			<!-- LEFT COLUMN: What mapaPH is -->
			<div class="lg:col-span-5 flex flex-col justify-start">
				<div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
					<span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-mapa-green">
						About the Project
					</span>
				</div>
				
				<h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-mapa-ink leading-tight">
					A collaborative ecosystem for spatial web tools.
				</h2>
				
				<div class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 mt-6 space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
					<p>
						mapaPH is an open-source community dedicated to building practical tools that use the map of the Philippines as their foundation. From GeoJSON downloads and boundary datasets to route planners, data visualizations, and location-based applications, we create focused projects that make Philippine geographic information easier to access, understand, and use.
					</p>
					<p>
						Every project is developed in the open, encouraging collaboration, knowledge sharing, and community contributions. Whether you're a developer, researcher, student, or GIS enthusiast, mapaPH provides a place to build, improve, and share tools that make Philippine spatial data more useful for everyone.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- RIGHT COLUMN: Core principles -->
			<div class="lg:col-span-7 flex flex-col justify-center">
				<div class="space-y-8">
					<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/80 pt-6">
						<h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-mapa-ink">
							Map-First by Default
						</h3>
						<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/80 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
							Every project starts with a map. Whether it's administrative boundaries, transportation networks, public facilities, demographic data, or geographic datasets, our applications are designed to help people explore, analyze, and interact with information through the Philippine map.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/80 pt-6">
						<h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-mapa-ink">
							Open-Source Collaboration
						</h3>
						<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/80 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
							Our projects are developed transparently on GitHub, where anyone can contribute ideas, report issues, improve code, or create entirely new map-based tools. We believe community collaboration leads to better software and more accessible geographic resources.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/80 pt-6">
						<h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-mapa-ink">
							Lightweight & Purpose-Driven
						</h3>
						<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/80 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
							Rather than building one massive GIS platform, we create focused applications that solve a single problem well. Each tool is fast, simple to use, and designed to be combined with others as the open-source ecosystem continues to grow.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
		</div>

		<!-- Bottom Disclaimer Note -->
		<div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-mapa-contour/60">
			<p class="font-sans text-xs text-mapa-ink/60 leading-relaxed italic max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
				Note: mapaPH is an independent, community-led open-source index. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or representative of the Philippine government or any of its municipal departments.
			</p>
		</div>
		
	</div>
</section>
